descriptionMarkdown:
- In the constant combinator, set the repeating interval of Hours Minutes and Seconds (H:M:S) that you would like a clock to reset
- Switch the combinator on
- The green power pole on the right is the clock counter on the green wire, green signal
- Every time the clock starts or resets the green signal is 0

Notes

- The green signal is ALWAYS zero when you switch off the combinator
- The screenshot includes concrete, the blueprint does not
- The H:M:S in the blueprint is preset to 0:0:5 and the combinator is off
- Play with the Green variable in the constant combinator at your peril, you may break the clock if you do
title: H:M:S Clock
